        "contenuto_esteso": "Death toll of strikes on Iran rises above 1,000, tens of thousands flee Tehran - France 24 Skip to main content To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. Accept Manage my choices One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Try again © France 24 07:01 Death toll of strikes on Iran rises above 1,000, tens of thousands flee Tehran Middle East Issued on: 04/03/2026 - 21:21 Share The United Nations on Wednesday said an estimated 100,000 people fled Tehran in the first two days of the US and Israeli strikes on Iran on February 28 and March 1. FRANCE 24\"s Reza Sayah reports from Iran, where the death toll has climbed over 1,000 people, with \"civilians bearing the brunt of this war\". Keywords for this article Iran Israel Strikes Middle East Read more Read less 'The fear for the Gulf countries is that the first client of the US would be Israel' 04/03/2026 Middle East US submarine torpedoed Iranian warship in Indian Ocean, Pentagon says 04/03/2026 Middle East 'Gambling for resurrection': Amid domestic crises, is US war on Iran a 'wag the dog' trump card? 04/03/2026 Middle East Spain accuses US of \"playing Russian roulette\" with millions of lives in Iran 04/03/2026 Middle East A look at who the frontrunners are for Iran's supreme leader position 04/03/2026 Middle East Countries work to secure safe passage in the Strait of Hormuz 04/03/2026 Middle East US sank Iranian warship, Pentagon announces in press briefing 04/03/2026 Middle East Replay: US Pentagon gives briefing on Iran as US and Israel continue to strike 04/03/2026 Americas First French repatriation flight lands in Paris from the Middle East 04/03/2026 Middle East Page not found The content you requested does not exist or is not available anymore."
