        "contenuto_esteso": "'The fear for the Gulf countries is that the first client of the US would be Israel' - France 24 Skip to main content To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. Accept Manage my choices One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Try again © France 24 06:50 'The fear for the Gulf countries is that the first client of the US would be Israel' Middle East Issued on: 04/03/2026 - 20:51 Modified: 04/03/2026 - 20:53 Share \"The US is under immense pressure to continue producing as many interceptors as it can, but the fear for the Gulf countries is that the first client of the US would be Israel, rather than the GCC\". Hoda Abdel-Hamid reports for FRANCE 24 from Doha in Qatar. Keywords for this article Iran GCC Qatar Bahrain Kuwait Read more Read less US submarine torpedoed Iranian warship in Indian Ocean, Pentagon says 04/03/2026 Middle East 'Gambling for resurrection': Amid domestic crises, is US war on Iran a 'wag the dog' trump card? 04/03/2026 Middle East Spain accuses US of \"playing Russian roulette\" with millions of lives in Iran 04/03/2026 Middle East A look at who the frontrunners are for Iran's supreme leader position 04/03/2026 Middle East Countries work to secure safe passage in the Strait of Hormuz 04/03/2026 Middle East US sank Iranian warship, Pentagon announces in press briefing 04/03/2026 Middle East Replay: US Pentagon gives briefing on Iran as US and Israel continue to strike 04/03/2026 Americas First French repatriation flight lands in Paris from the Middle East 04/03/2026 Middle East Iran war opens cracks within Trump's MAGA base 04/03/2026 Middle East Page not found The content you requested does not exist or is not available anymore."
