        "contenuto_esteso": "US submarine torpedoed Iranian warship in Indian Ocean, Pentagon says - France 24 Skip to main content To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. Accept Manage my choices One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Try again © France 24 01:57 US submarine torpedoed Iranian warship in Indian Ocean, Pentagon says Middle East Issued on: 04/03/2026 - 20:23 Share A US submarine sank an Iranian warship in the Indian Ocean, Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth said Wednesday, touting the strike as evidence of America's global reach in its war on Iran. \"An American submarine sunk an Iranian warship that thought it was safe in international waters. Instead, it was sunk by a torpedo,\" Hegseth told a news conference. FRANCE 24's James Vasina reports. Video by: James VASINA Keywords for this article Iran Navy Sri Lanka Indian Ocean Read more Read less 'Gambling for resurrection': Amid domestic crises, is US war on Iran a 'wag the dog' trump card? 04/03/2026 Middle East Spain accuses US of \"playing Russian roulette\" with millions of lives in Iran 04/03/2026 Middle East A look at who the frontrunners are for Iran's supreme leader position 04/03/2026 Middle East Countries work to secure safe passage in the Strait of Hormuz 04/03/2026 Middle East US sank Iranian warship, Pentagon announces in press briefing 04/03/2026 Middle East Replay: US Pentagon gives briefing on Iran as US and Israel continue to strike 04/03/2026 Americas First French repatriation flight lands in Paris from the Middle East 04/03/2026 Middle East Iran war opens cracks within Trump's MAGA base 04/03/2026 Middle East Broadest evacuation order for Lebanon issued by Israeli army 04/03/2026 Middle East Page not found The content you requested does not exist or is not available anymore."
